==Translingual==
====Etymology====
From ''p'', denoting negative logarithm, and ''H'', denoting hydrogen.

===Abbreviation===
'''pH''' (''functioning as a noun''; ''plural'' '''pHs''')

#The negative of the [[logarithm]] to the base 10 of the concentration of [[hydrogen]] ions, measured in [[mole]]s per liter; a measure of acidity or alkalinity of a substance, which takes numerical values from 0 (maximum acidity) through 7 (neutral) to 14 (maximum alkalinity).

====See also====
*[[pOH]], [[pK]], [[PH]]

